The paper discusses the use of neural networks for solving differential equations, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of polynomial neural networks, which is a specific type of neural network architecture, and machine learning techniques for fitting the weights of the network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of these techniques for simulating dynamical systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and scientific computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Taylor maps, which is a mathematical technique for approximating functions, and this falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
